      "content": "Hey there, thanks for reaching out. I'd be happy to help you draft a rejection email that maintains a positive relationship with this strong candidate. You can express gratitude for their impressive system design skills and cultural alignment while gently explaining that the decision was based on specific technical requirements for the cloud stack. Keeping the tone professional and forward-looking will ensure we don't burn the bridge. Here is a draft you can use:\n\nSubject: Update on Senior Developer Application – [Candidate Name]\n\nDear [Candidate Name],\n\nThank you for making it to the final round for our Senior Developer position in Austin. We were truly impressed by your deep understanding of system design and the excellent cultural fit you demonstrated during our interviews. While your profile is outstanding, we have decided to move forward with a candidate who possesses slightly more direct experience with our specific cloud stack.\n\nWe sincerely appreciate the time you took to share your expertise with us and would love to stay in touch for future opportunities. Please feel free to reach out if you have any questions.\n\nBest regards,\n\n[Your Name]\n[Your Title]",
      "source": "target",
