    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That is a great idea; adding a personal touch will make the candidate feel valued rather than just another data point in a spreadsheet. You can acknowledge the fierce competition and the high standards required for our Austin team to explain why this specific choice was made, while still emphasizing how much you enjoyed getting to know them. Here is a revised draft with that extra warmth:\n\nSubject: Great meeting you – Senior Developer Role\n\nDear [Candidate Name],\n\nIt was a genuine pleasure getting to know you during our final round for the Senior Developer position in Austin. We were incredibly impressed by your system design skills and the way you naturally fit into our team's culture. The process was absolutely competitive this year, and we held a very high bar to ensure we found the perfect fit for our growing team.\n\nWhile we ultimately decided to move forward with a candidate who has slightly more direct experience with our specific cloud stack, it was a tough choice because you were a top contender. We truly appreciate the time you invested and would love to stay in touch for future opportunities.\n\nWarmly,\n\n[Your Name]\n[Your Title]",
